==English==

===Etymology===
based on the fact that the strategy would not work on a moonlit night, such that the would-be pirate cussed the moon

===Noun===
'''mooncusser'''
# A land-based [[pirate]], who on dark nights along dangerous coasts would erect deliberately misleading decoy [[signal fire]]s and then, after having induced a [[shipwreck]], plunder the wreckage for valuables.

===Synonyms===
* [[wrecker]]

